cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.CC

The paper discusses the use of memristors in neural network architectures, specifically in the implementation of perceptrons. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also touches on topics related to electronic engineering, such as memristor technology (cs.ET - Emerging Technologies) and circuit design (cs.AR - Hardware Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of memristors in synapses and non-volatile memories (cs.SY - Systems and Control), and the adaptation of learning systems to a memristor-based paradigm (cs.CC - Computational Complexity).
